         <abstract>
            <p>We present a sampling theorem for locally compact abelian groups. The sampling sets are finite unions of cosets of a closed subgroup. This generalizes the well-known case of nonequidistant but periodic sampling on the real line. For nonbandlimited functions an L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;-type estimate for the aliasing error is given. We discuss the application of the theorem to a class of sampling sets in R&lt;sup&gt;s&lt;/sup&gt;, give a general algorithm for a computer implementation, present a detailed description of the implementation for the s-dimensional torus group, and point out connections to lattice rules for numerical integration.</p>
          </abstract>
